    <title>Refugees contributor: Sharon Ekambaram</title>
    <description>Sharon Ekambaram is head of the Refugee and Migrant Rights Project at Lawyers for Human Rights. Before joining LHR she worked for Doctors Without Borders as the founding director of the organization’s Southern Africa office and later as the head of the advocacy and networking program. She also worked with the Treatment Action Campaign at its inception in the struggle for access to treatment for people living with HIV and AIDS, and later worked for the AIDS Consortium. Twitter: Sharon Ekambaram.
 
 
